This paper is about language modelling using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of distributed vector representations and sparse random projections, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method on a specific dataset, which falls under cs.SD (Sound).
